{"id":14881841,"mediaExerciseId":"624a26bb-7ccd-47d5-80d2-1082ffff5dbb","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612488,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":789,"solutions":[{"id":6028900,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"The financial engineer can sell forward contracts since this is similar to buying a put option. Generally, a put option is used if there is an expected decline in the price of the commodity. This has the same function as selling a forward contract. \n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/175f5b542099f6fccc935477d3e762f3/0b6234d509fc10be8294d66901f94932/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/175f5b542099f6fccc935477d3e762f3/0b6234d509fc10be8294d66901f94932/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The general relationship between put option, call option, and forward contract is that buying a forward contract is similar to buying a call option while selling a forward contract is similar to buying a put option since calls and puts function in the opposite direction of the market.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/175f5b542099f6fccc935477d3e762f3/a74d31917f85f93938325728a372f2ec/lateximg_large.png","width":1011},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/175f5b542099f6fccc935477d3e762f3/a74d31917f85f93938325728a372f2ec/lateximg.png","width":506}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"c75b218e-4cd9-4f63-b0e4-d17608e5a641","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":nul